timelineItems.name: Jason Baum
timelineItems.text: Denis Hamlett suited up for tonight’s game and we are underway at Red Bull Arena #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Peter Nolan
timelineItems.text: I hate to be obvious, but Lloyd Sam makes a big difference to this Red Bull team. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Craig Forde
timelineItems.text: The #NERevs defense is in a very, very bad place right now, time to start stocking up on bodies and put pressure on the positions

timelineItems.name: John Corbett
timelineItems.text: Twist and Shout, @RBA_SouthWard ! #RBNY #NYvNE http://t.co/JhkQJMRURX

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Nice sequence of passing between most of the attack, with BWP springing Sam to return the favor. 2-0 and it's only the 10th minute. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Matt LaPan
timelineItems.text: Heaps said he wanted the Revs to outwork the Red Bulls. Through 10 minutes that isnt happening. Horrible start #NERevs

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  New York Red Bulls 3, New England Revolution 0. Bradley Wright-Phillips (New York Red Bulls) right footed shot from the center of the box.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Bradley Wright-Phillips and the Red Bulls continue to carve up the Revs defense

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Red Bulls just sliced and diced the Revs midfield and defense on about 6 quick passes. Jermaine, where art thou!!! #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Navdeep Cattry
timelineItems.text: Jesse should get ejected every week if we play like this! #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC will have some work to do if they want to keep 2nd place in the East. #NYRB already up 3-0 less than 15 minutes in.

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Red Bulls had scored just three goals in the opening 15 minutes so far this year. So they just doubled their production. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Not saying that Jones prevents those 3 goals, but after the 1st one, Jones is the player who gets these guys re-focused. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Renny Swan
timelineItems.text: All the "right" words during the week are so much air when we look so broken weeks in a row. C'mon, turn this around already! #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Eric Giacometti
timelineItems.text: One from the training ground on that set piece & it nearly came off. Lots more attention to dead ball situations under Marsch this yr #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: What a beautiful set piece from RBNY. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Eric Giacometti
timelineItems.text: A #NERevs goal is wiped out by the offside flag... but the head ref is going over to confer with his AR. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Strike that. GOAL AWARDED. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: My guess is the linesman thought Davies (who was offside) got a touch. He did not. Great job by Alan Kelly to sort it out. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: AttitudeAJM
timelineItems.text: 4' Pressure early from #NYRevs as #RBNY can't get a hold on offense. #MLS #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: Matt LaPan
timelineItems.text: No surprise but @MidnightRiders & @NErebellion sound loud on the broadcast. Best fans in MLs #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Taylor Twellman
timelineItems.text: Phenomenal job from the middle ref Alan Kelly in #NYvNE to get the call correct with his assistant on the sideline.

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: That's Andy Dorman's first regular-season goal since returning to the #NERevs in 2013, although he did score in the playoffs that year.

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Halftime whistle blows. A slightly comfortable 3-1 lead for the home side. But only slightly. #NYvNE

timelineItems.text: Tierney is a problem. He has to play cautiously with BWP, and it makes it easier for NYRB To neutralize Bunbury #doublewhammy. #NERevs

timelineItems.text: Scott Caldwell had just 13 touches in first half, 2nd fewest on #NERevs. #NYvNE

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls

timelineItems.text: Who wouldve ever thought Andy Dorman would be the primary scoring threat. Guy is playing with some serious passion right now #NERevs

timelineItems.name: James J Pepe
timelineItems.text: BWP with the simplest of headers. 1-0. #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Tyler
timelineItems.text: Never thought I'd say this but watching Andy Dorman is a treat right now #NERevs
